# Database — Migrations Rules

**Never** modify the database schema directly.

Always create **migrations** for schema changes.

- One logical change per migration when possible
- Migrations must be reversible (provide downgrade/rollback)
- Do not commit broken or half-applied migrations
- Test migrations on a copy of data before production

Use the project’s migration tool (e.g. Alembic, Django migrations) consistently.
